  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 196.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, sure.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As I have told you, Star Street, which branched off from the center of town at Main, Main Street, was for a long stretch almost completely Jewish.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And perhaps, I can give you an indication of an interesting element of the economy of the Jewish community.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "On the other side of Star Street, the first building was an apothecary, of course owned by Jews.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because the apothecary, the, the chemist, as they would be called-- and of course, was a professional.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And therefore, he was a Jew.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "With the rarest exception, so were all the doctors and lawyers.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then next to it, you would have, for instance, the beadle living across the street from the main synagogue, which was known as the shul.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he was, so to say, the custodian of the, of the main shul.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The Jewish community itself, it was almost a kind of a closed economy, where the, the community, to serve its religious and communal needs, in effect was a very substantial employer, and where em-- employment almost created a, a kind of a dynasty.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "If you were the beadle of the, of the shul, and you eventually had your son or son-in-law take over for you.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "If you were a shohet or, or a ritual slaughterer, as for instance, was a Mechel in our town, then when you married off one of your daughters toward a Gimpel or maybe it was a, a Mechel who was the, the son-in-law and then Gimpel was the father-in-law.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I don't know exactly at this point.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Then, in effect, your dowry for your daughter was your becoming also a ritual slaughterer in town.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And if you were the one who maintained the [NON-ENGLISH], then your, your son-in-law or your son eventually took over that position.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
